reviewText: I love this series and I watch it whenever it is on. I like how all of the guys interact with each other and that threw all of the chaos they create the most beautiful cars and bikes I have ever seen,

I've been a fan of Counting Cars since it first came on.  I really like the show (and others) on DVD because I can watch a bunch of episodes one after another.  I would have liked it more if it had a blooper reel or other outtakes.

If you like the show, buy this one when the price is right.

13 Episodes on 2 Discs= FUN! Starting with You Talkin' to Me? & ending with Day of Judgement. Features include:Count's Coffin Couch, Chumlee & his Lincoln Flip & Lyle & Beverly. If U Dig Danny, you'll LUV this!
Great TV series for the Weekend Car Mechanic!!!  The characters are one of a kind.  I love how they cruise for new projects on the road and neighborhoods.
Great series waiting for season 3.  We visited the shop this summer and they treat you well.  Would buy again every year.
Quite an amazing small TV. Particularly handy is the DVD slot on the side. Very, very thorough remote control. Great addition to the kitchen.
Perfect part of the show and for my movie collection
This was a Christmas present and my sister and brother in law loved it.
Love this show! Watch every chance I get. If it's not on tv, the DVD is playing.
The entertaining Danny Coker -- the Count -- refurbishes classic car. He is quite a character and eminently professional in reconstituting these cars.

NOT AS GOOD AS YOU THINK. YOU WOULD HAVE TO A G@Y DRUG ADDICT LIKE DANNY TO WATCH OR ENJOY THIS MESS. WHY WOULD ANYONE NORMAL WATCH THIS. GO TO THE NEAREST MECHANIC SHOP TO GET YOUR FIX. IT'LL BE WAY BETTER THAN THIS MESS.

This show has some great cars and rebuild in it. The story lines are solid. The crew is fun. I have visited the garage and it was just great to see everything. I will watch this show over and over again.
Excellent tv show!  My husband and I both love it!

Just a good fun show.  Got  it for my husband but  really bought it to watch Danny,  now I'm into the cars and trying to figure out what the formula is to figure horse power.  My husband says I can watch Danny as long as he can watch the cars.
He says he's buying me season 3  for my birthday.
I have enjoyed Counting Cars since it first appeared on the History Channel. I bought this copy as a present for my boss. He really loves it as well.
Danny Joker and his crew are awesome at what they do.
I bought these for my husband for Father's Day. He loved it. It was a great price, no damage from shipping and received them quickly.
